I wrote a small patch to fix some small issue&#13;
- BOM at the begin of a PHP file (see [1])&#13;
- fixed some minor coding standards issues (tabs, missing spaces, ...)&#13;
- replace a call to ereg by preg_match to be PHP 5.3 compliant&#13;
&#13;
This patch is available here : http://pwet.fr/content/download/73110/224590/file/bom_cs_php53_birthday.patch&#13;
&#13;
In addition it would be nice to make this extension compatible with 4.1 and 4.2 by removing references to eZDomDocument as mentioned in [2].&#13;
&#13;
[1] http://projects.ez.no/birthday/forum/general/utf_8_bom_header&#13;
