      <title>UTF-8 BOM header</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/birthday/forum/general/utf_8_bom_header</link>
      <description>Hi Georg&#13;
&#13;
The ezbirthdaytype.php file apparently contains a UTF-8 BOM header, which causes certain browsers like Firefox to show some weird characters at the top of the page. See http://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-utf8-bom for more details.&#13;
&#13;
This is valid for at least the 1.0 branch, I did not test it on trunk.&#13;
&#13;
Could you fix this by removing the BOM header? Thanks.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Kristof Coomans)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/birthday/forum/general/utf_8_bom_header</guid>
