    <item>
      <title>Adding some date arithmetic operators to this datatype?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/birthday/forum/general/adding_some_date_arithmetic_operators_to_this_datatype</link>
      <description>It would be much more useful to use "universal dates" for doing date math than the standard unix-timestamp based date: you can carry out operation on timestamps, but when tou go back to date representation, you're screwed if ending up before the epoch.&#13;
&#13;
Suggestions:&#13;
a) allow strtotime format, such as modify('+1 day'), [the 'php way', not too friendly really] or&#13;
b) pick a date math implementation from another implementation, such eg as the oracle one (http://www.psoug.org/reference/date_func.html)</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Gaetano Giunta)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/birthday/forum/general/adding_some_date_arithmetic_operators_to_this_datatype</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 06 Mar 2008 12:14:29 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
